                {
                    "name": "Expel Infestation",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "text": "The isqulug expels larvae from the hivemind in its head in a 30-foot cone. Creatures in this area take 6d10 piercing damage as the swarm feeds on their flesh (DC 30 basic Reflex save). Any creature that takes damage is exposed to isqulugia. The isqulug becomes <a aonid=\"37\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">stupefied 1</a> for 1d4 rounds, during which it can't Expel Infestation.",
                    "subtype": "offensive_action",
                    "action": {
                        "type": "stat_block_section",
                        "subtype": "action",
                        "name": "Two Actions",
                        "image": "TwoActions.png"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Isqulugia",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "text": "Isqulugia's <a aonid=\"34\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">sickened</a>, <a aonid=\"35\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">slowed</a>, and <a aonid=\"28\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">paralyzed</a> conditions can't be removed until this affliction is removed; <b>Saving Throw</b> DC 30 Fortitude; <b>Stage 1</b> sickened 1 (1 hour); <b>Stage 2</b> <a aonid=\"15\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">fatigued</a> and sickened 2 (1 day); <b>Stage 3</b> fatigued and slowed 1 (1 day); <b>Stage 4</b> paralyzed (1 day); <b>Stage 5</b>the creature dies, and its body violently transforms into a new isqulug. <a aonid=\"377\" game-obj=\"Spells\"><i>Wish</i></a>, similar magic, or a 9th-level <a aonid=\"20\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">resurrect</a> ritual can return the victim to life. The new isqulug remains even if the victim is brought back to life.",
